- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
- preceed should activate network if no DHCP is available
  - interface names:
    - mini: eno1, wlp0s20f3
    - h1: enp5s0, wlp6s0
    - h9: enp2s0, wlp3s0, wlx04bad6cb783c
    One can use a usb network card. Its name will be enx + mac address, which
    can be obtained in advance, before building an iso image.
    Example: enx00133bfbb0a7
    Docs: systemd.net-naming-scheme, consistent_network_device_naming
    Works during install, but does not activate it after reboot.
    Note: busybox ip does not implement all ip functionality - it does not understand
    interface alternative names
  - when using 'auto' for network interface name (netcfg/choose_interface select auto)
    it could pick either a wired or wireless interface.
    Make sure you have a proper routing to that interface's ip:
    either directly connect wires, or add a specific route for that ip.
    Note: 'auto' was problematic - all links were down (physical connnection problem?)
- during the install the installer ssh is listening on port 22
  - connect: ssh -p 22 root@host
  - attach to screen: screen -DR -e ^Ff
  - continue with the install if it's available inside screen.
    Otherwise, manually run debian-installer
  - after the install and boot, the ssh is listening on the configured port,
    6322 in this example
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

before finishing installation, switch to other console, then install and configure dropbear:

copy deb packages to the target (or copy them into the installation media in advance):
dropbear-initramfs, dropbear-bin

mount -o bind /sys /target/sys
mount -o bind /dev /target/dev
mount -o bind /proc /target/proc
chroot /target

dpkg -i xxxxxxx
  or (if the installation media contains it)
apt-get install dropbear-initramfs

add your key to /etc/dropbear/initramfs/authorized_keys
configure dropbear in /etc/dropbear/initramfs/dropbear.conf
  DROPBEAR_OPTIONS="-I 300 -j -k -p 6322 -s -c cryptroot-unlock"
configure network if necessary: /etc/initramfs-tools/initramfs.conf
generate initramfs: update-initramfs -u
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
or use p2.diff:

diff --git a/preseed.cfg b/preseed.cfg
